      {
        "id": 1955777,
        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2016-06-21T19:52:09.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I tried the 2012 earlier this year. A lovely wine, with striking briary, wild berry &amp; plum fruit tones. While it has a very different personality to Dominus, it is very much in the same style, so if you appreciate Dominus then I\u2019m sure you\u2019ll like Ulysses. The site is not far from the boundary with Yountville, up against the western hills pretty much behind the Brix restaurant. So it\u2019s just a bit of a way from To Kalon and Martha\u2019s. I was a big fan and thoroughly recommend it.</p>\n<p>My brief write-up\u2019s here: <a href=\"http://www.decanter.com/wine-news/inside-the-new-moueix-napa-project-ulysses-290275/\" class=\"inline-onebox\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Producer profile: Ulysses - Decanter</a></p>",
